==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Partialist
<hw>Par"tial*ist</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who is
partial.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>One who holds that the atonement
was made only for a part of mankind, that is, for the elect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Partiality</ent>⟦br⟧
